blocks: <p><h3>2 Comments.</h3>Comments by RadRob:</p><p><a class="url http outside" href="http://zhurnaly.com/cgi-bin/wiki?action=browse;id=ZhurnalyWiki_CSS_Experiments;css=http://zhurnaly.com/zhurnaly_right_gotobar.css">GoToBar on Right</a> looks good - only problem is that the sidebar is half the width, instead of some fixed number of ems. (I'd go with ems so that it scales properly with changing font size - define sidebar as 15 ems and main text as 30 ems or remaining width, whichever is larger, and I think it'll look good even if the user changes their font size.)</p><p>Having tested all of these on the iPhone and on the MacBook &mdash; the latter with Firefox, Safari, Google Chrome, and Stainless &mdash; I would have to say that the house style has the nicest edit box but otherwise I'm indifferent between that, Pastel, and NoPastel.</p><p>-- RadRob 2010-03-01 09:42 UTC</p><hr /><p>tnx Robin! --- this browser on the HP netbook seems to have strange problems sometimes with reverting to the default stylesheet ... I have to quit and restart to clear the cache (maybe) ... many thanks for your tests and comments! <em><strong>^z</strong></em></p><p>-- <a class="url http outside" href="http://zhurnaly.com">zz</a> 2010-03-01 09:57 UTC</p>
