text: === 2 Comments. ===
	Comments by RadRob:
	
	[[http://zhurnaly.com/cgi-bin/wiki?action=browse;id=ZhurnalyWiki_CSS_Experiments;css=http://zhurnaly.com/zhurnaly_right_gotobar.css|GoToBar on Right]] looks good - only problem is that the sidebar is half the width, instead of some fixed number of ems. (I'd go with ems so that it scales properly with changing font size - define sidebar as 15 ems and main text as 30 ems or remaining width, whichever is larger, and I think it'll look good even if the user changes their font size.)
	
	Having tested all of these on the iPhone and on the MacBook &mdash; the latter with Firefox, Safari, Google Chrome, and Stainless &mdash; I would have to say that the house style has the nicest edit box but otherwise I'm indifferent between that, Pastel, and NoPastel.
	
